                                                        <div class="col-md-7">
                                                            <div class="main-body">
                                                                <p>To be a <strong> volunteer mentor </strong>, all you need is two hours a week and a caring heart. Other requirements include:</p>
                                                                <ul>
                                                                    <li>Age 23 or older</li>
                                                                    <li>Pass a fingerprint security screening</li>
                                                                    <li>Complete 21+ hours of comprehensive training to understand cultural/social development, mental health issues, risk factors, and to learn ways to engage in positive, fun activities at the Y and communicate/relate to youth</li>
                                                                    <li>Meet with your mentee two hours a week for one year</li>
                                                                </ul> 
                                                                <p>Requirements to participate in Reach and Rise as a <strong> mentee </strong> include:</p>   
                                                                <ul>
                                                                    <li>Youth ages 6 – 18</li>
                                                                    <li>Resident of Baltimore City or Anne Arundel, Baltimore, Carroll, Harford, or Howard County</li>
                                                                    <li>Family/guardians who are committed to Building Futures</li>
                                                                </ul>    
                                                                <p>If you are interested in volunteering as an adult mentor (or know a child you’d like to refer to Reach and Rise), please contact any one of our Reach and Rise coordinators.</p>
